This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new approach to actor-critic reinforcement learning algorithms with experience replay. It also discusses the bias-variance tradeoffs in V-trace, a form of importance sampling for actor-critic methods, which is a common topic in machine learning. Additionally, the paper provides extensive empirical validation of the proposed solution, which is a key aspect of machine learning research. 

The paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with reinforcement learning algorithms, which are a subset of AI. 

Furthermore, the paper could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) as reinforcement learning is a popular technique in robotics for training agents to perform tasks. 

The paper could also be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it discusses the stability of off-policy learning, which is a key aspect of control systems. 

Finally, the paper could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it demonstrates state-of-the-art data efficiency on Atari, which is a popular benchmark for computer vision and machine learning algorithms.
